## Naming Convention
- **GRIT** — formal product name (used in UI, docs, repo)
- **Squeaky Wheel** — informal working name (used in conversation)

## Stack
- Language: Python 3.13
- Frontend: Streamlit
- Database: SQLite (`grit_cache.db`)
- Automation: GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/daily_sync.yml`)
- Secrets: `.streamlit/secrets.toml` (local only, never committed)
- Virtual env: `venv/` (activate with `source venv/bin/activate`)

## Project Purpose
Political integrity "Truth Engine" — tracks Australian MPs, their voting records,
media statements, and surfaces rhetoric vs. reality conflicts.

## Key Files
- `app.py` — Streamlit frontend
- `build_schema.py` — initialises SQLite tables (run once)
- `sync_data.py` — nightly data sync (also run by GitHub Actions)
- `grit_cache.db` — local database (committed to repo for portability)

## DB Tables
- `politicians` (ID, name)
- `bills` (Bill_No, title)
- `media` (URL, MP_ID, text)
